      li.slide: a(target="_blank", href="http://vallandingham.me/racial_divide/#dn") Racial Divide

  section.slide
    h2 What is it?
    blockquote
      p D3.js is a JavaScript library for manipulating documents based on data... D3 allows you to bind arbitrary data to a Document Object Model (DOM), and then apply data-driven transformations to the document.
      p: cite: a(href="http://d3js.org") d3js.org

  section.slide
    h2 What is it really?
    p Collection of tools for producing many different kinds of visualizations
    ul
      li.slide Loading external data
      li.slide Maps and topography
      li.slide HTML/SVG/CSS manipulation
      li.slide Scales: linear, log, color, ordinal...
      li.slide Layouts: networks, axes, histograms, trees, packs, bundles...
      li.slide Interactivity
      li.slide Animations
      li.slide Math

  section.slide
    h2 How does it work?
    ul
      li.slide Links your data to HTML/SVG elements
      li.slide Edits your webpage on-the-fly
      li.slide Executes transformations based on user input

  section.slide
    h1 Usage Warning

